          </div>

          <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-red-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-800 mb-4">âŒ Avoid This</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">âœ—</span>
                <span>Vague subject descriptions ("math stuff")</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">âœ—</span>
                <span>Ignoring student context</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">âœ—</span>
                <span>Using prompts without reviewing them first</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">âœ—</span>
                <span>Expecting perfection on first try</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">âœ—</span>
                <span>Being too generic in requirements</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

